{"person":{"id":"HD0794","has_descendants_documented":true,"prominent_name_reason":"Frances Livingston Hart Butler (1816-1895) married Rev. Clement Moore Butler (1810-1890) — 36th Chaplain of the United States Senate 1850-1853. Butler delivered funeral addresses for Senator John C. Calhoun (Apr 1, 1850) and Senator Henry Clay (Jul 1, 1852). He also served as chaplain at the ordination by Bishop Benjamin Treadwell Onderdonk — Onderdonk was subsequently suspended after multiple women alleged he made improper advances, including toward Mrs. Butler in a carriage the evening before her husband's ordination. Butler later served as rector in Rome, Italy 1861-1864 and professor of ecclesiastical history at the Divinity School of the Protestant Episcopal Church, Philadelphia until 1884. Frances was \"a niece of Richard Channing Moore, Bishop of Virginia.\" Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clement_Moore_Butler","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1816,"month":10,"day":24,"city":"Henrico County","state":"Virginia"},"death":{"year":1895,"month":8,"day":1,"city":"Germantown","state":"Pennsylvania"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM028","plot_notes":"Woodlands Cemetery, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania"},"parents":{"father_id":"H01564","mother_id":"X00164"},"marriages":[{"children_ids":["HD0796","HD0797","HD0798"],"spouse_id":"X01318","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1836,"location_city":"Washington","location_state":"DC"}],"tags":[],"sources":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":[],"primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clement_Moore_Butler","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia","notable_blurb":"Wife of US Senate chaplain Clement Moore Butler"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Frances Livingston Hart Butler","